<title>JAPAN: BOJ &quot;tankan&quot; shows Japan firms see more spending.</title>
<headline>BOJ &quot;tankan&quot; shows Japan firms see more spending.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-04-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Major Japanese companies plan a 2.7 percent increase in capital investment in fiscal 1997/98, following a 4.7 percent rise in the previous year, the Bank of Japan (BOJ) said in its March &quot;tankan&quot; short-term corporate survey released on Wednesday.</p>
